{"build_type":"library","description":"Give the CALLING (worker) thread its own private bump arena and CLEAN thread-local state: set FS base to the carved block (arch_prctl), init the six per-thread arena globals, then ZERO every lazy-init thread-local global (file-read buffers, catalog/discovery state, sha tables, and the loader shelf g_ld_region/map/loaded/cursor) so each worker self-initializes them in its OWN arena on first use (establish-if-zero) regardless of a recycled block's stale bytes — the single fix for the whole 'launched worker has opt-in zeroed globals' bug class. g_ld_libdir is NOT zeroed; it is propagated from the parent via arena block slot 64 (set only when present, so bootstrap/unprovisioned endows keep the resolve-closure libdir). Slice 3: sets g_arena_fixed=0 so a worker that exhausts its 4 MiB seed GROWS from the pool (acquire-arena-chunk), and reads g_arena_budget from the block[82] budget-guard cell (2 GiB) instead of the seed size, so the guard bounds a worker while the pool is the true bound.","module_name":"endow-calling-thread-with-private-arena","package_name":"endow-calling-thread-with-private-arena","function_definitions":{"endow-calling-thread-with-private-arena":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"block","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"six","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":6},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"hdr","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1024},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"i82","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":82},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"slot_libdir","variable_type":"i64","assi